{"kind":"overview","metadata":{"title":"Building SyncUps","category":"Building SyncUps","categoryPathComponent":"BuildingSyncUps","estimatedTime":"3hr 10min","role":"overview"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[],"reference":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps"},"sections":[{"kind":"hero","title":"Building SyncUps","action":{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started","type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps"},"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"chapters":[{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps"],"image":"chapter1.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recreation of the Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"What is SyncUps?"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps"],"image":"chapter2.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app evolves."}]}],"name":"Lists of sync-ups"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm"],"image":"chapter3.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s build a new feature for editing the details of a sync-up in a form. This will allow us to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"explore the binding tools the library provides, and we will add some complex logic around focus"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the form, and show how it is 100% testable."}]}],"name":"New sync-up form"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation"],"image":"chapter4.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We now have two features built, the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"add that sync-up to the root list.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Presenting the sync-up form"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps"],"image":"chapter5.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Applications typically need to persist data across application launches. The Composable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Architecture comes with tools to help you persist your application’s data."}]}],"name":"Persisting sync-ups to disk"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail"],"image":"chapter6.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The next feature to build is the “detail” screen for a sync-up. This feature allows the user to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edit a sync-up, record a new meeting, see past recorded meetings, and even delete the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sync-up."}]}],"name":"Sync-up detail"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation"],"image":"chapter7.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have a sync-up detail screen, but still no way to navigate to it from the rest of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"app. We want to be able to drill-down to the detail screen from the list screen."}]}],"name":"Navigating to sync-up detail"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer"],"image":"chapter8.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app is almost complete! But we have saved the most difficult feature for last: recording"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a new meeting. This requires interfacing with two complex dependencies, a speech recognizer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and timer, and requires some subtle behavior that we are definitely going to want to get"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test coverage on."}]}],"name":"Record meeting"}],"kind":"volume","content":[],"name":null,"image":null}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation":{"role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","kind":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We have now integrated two moderately complex features, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpsList"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so its time to write some tests. This will give us the opportunity to prove that the features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"work in tandem as we expect, and we will explore “non-exhaustive” testing to make our tests less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fragile."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation","title":"Testing the add sync-up flow","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupformpresentation"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingListOfSyncUps":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testinglistofsyncups","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUpsList feature we have built so far isn’t very complex. In fact, it only has one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"primary action, that of deleting sync-ups from its collection. However, it can be good practice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to test new features as you add them, and in the future we will have much more complicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior to test."}],"title":"Testing the list of sync-ups","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps","role":"project","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"5min"},"chapter2.png":{"identifier":"chapter2.png","alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter2.png"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpForm":{"estimatedTime":"10min","title":"Testing the sync-up form","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have a moderately complex feature for editing the details of a sync-up, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reducer. Let’s get some test coverage on the feature, and doing so will force us to come"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"face-to-face with dependencies for the first time in this tutorial."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupform","type":"topic","kind":"project","role":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/WhatIsSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/whatissyncups","title":"What is SyncUps?","kind":"project","role":"project","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recreation of Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application."}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingNavigation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","kind":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We have now implemented a navigation stack at the root of our application, and integrated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"3 features into the stack: the "},{"code":"SyncUpsList","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" feature, the "},{"code":"SyncUpDetail","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" feature, and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"MeetingView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Some of these features have quite complex logic binding them together, such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when one deletes a sync-up from the detail screen it should pop the screen off the stack."}],"title":"Testing navigation","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingnavigation"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PersistingSyncUps":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that we have the ability to add and remove sync-ups from the application, let’s add some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"persistence. This will involve using the “shared state” tools from the library, such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps","kind":"project","role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/persistingsyncups","type":"topic","title":"Persisting sync-ups","estimatedTime":"5min"},"chapter6.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"chapter6.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter6.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"chapter8.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"chapter8.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter8.png"}]},"chapter7.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"chapter7.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter7.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"chapter5.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"chapter5.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter5.png"}]},"chapter1.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"chapter1.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter1.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"chapter4.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"chapter4.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter4.png"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer":{"role":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingspeechrecognizer","kind":"project","type":"topic","title":"Adding a speech recognizer","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We have just one feature left to implement, and it’s one of the most complicated ones. We need"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to use Apple’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SFSpeechRecognizer"},{"type":"text","text":" API to ask the user for permission to transcribe their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"audio, and then start a speech recognition task to live transcribe the meeting while it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in progress."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer","estimatedTime":"10min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/BuildingSyncUps":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability."}],"title":"Building SyncUps","kind":"overview","role":"overview","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ListsOfSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app evolves."}],"title":"Lists of sync-ups","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/listsofsyncups","role":"project","type":"topic"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetail":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetail","role":"project","title":"Sync-up detail","type":"topic","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The “sync-up detail” screen shows all the information of a sync-up, and has many actions that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can take place in the screen. The user can edit the sync-up, or start a new meeting in the sync"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"up, or drill-down to a past meeting, or even delete the meeting."}],"estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingTimer":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingtimer","type":"topic","title":"Adding a meeting timer","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","role":"project","estimatedTime":"25min","kind":"project","abstract":[{"text":"The first major piece of logic and behavior we will introduce to the record meeting feature is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the timer. This is a long-living effect that runs in parallel with the rest of the feature, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"we need to implement nuanced logic to figure out when to proceed to the next speaker.","type":"text"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetailNavigation":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We will wrap the application built so far in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationStack"},{"type":"text","text":" so that we can navigate to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the detail screen. To do this we will create a new root-level feature that will be responsible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for implementing the logic of the stack and integrating all of the features together."}],"title":"Navigating to a sync-up detail","role":"project","estimatedTime":"20min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetailnavigation","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation","kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpDetail":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupdetail","type":"topic","kind":"project","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"SyncUpDetail","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" feature has slowly become quite complex. It now handles two forms of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"navigation (an alert and sheet), it models navigation state with a single enum, and it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"updates the parent feature via a shared property. It’s about time we got some test","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coverage on this feature so we can be sure it works as we expect, and so that we can make future","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes with confidence.","type":"text"}],"title":"Testing the sync-up detail","estimatedTime":"10min","role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpForm":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupform","kind":"project","title":"Sync-up form","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We will create a new feature with the Composable Architecture that is capable of editing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"details of a new sync-up. We will also add some nuanced logic around how focus moves through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"feature to make things a little more interesting."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm","estimatedTime":"15min","role":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PresentingSyncUpForm":{"type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/presentingsyncupform","kind":"project","title":"Presenting the sync-up form","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have two features built: the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"add that sync-up to the root list."}],"estimatedTime":"10min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/MeetingNavigation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation","estimatedTime":"5min","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that we have a navigation stack in place we can start navigating to other features in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application. The simplest is the meeting screen, which allows you to see the details of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"previous recorded meeting."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/meetingnavigation","title":"Navigating to a meeting","role":"project","kind":"project"},"chapter3.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"chapter3.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter3.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/RecordMeetingFeature":{"type":"topic","title":"The RecordMeeting feature","role":"project","kind":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/recordmeetingfeature","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s get the basics of a new feature into place that we can navigate to, and then we will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"slowly layer on its complex logic and behavior, such as the timer and speech recognizer."}],"estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp":{"title":"Editing and deleting a sync-up","type":"topic","kind":"project","role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s implement two major pieces of functionality in the detail screen: editing the sync-up and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deleting the sync-up. This will force us to face a number of common problems in app development"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all at once, including view reuse, navigation, alerts, and parent-child communication patterns."}],"estimatedTime":"30min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/editinganddeletingsyncup","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp"}}}